President Donald J. Trump visited Bethlehem and was warmly welcomed by President Mahmoud Abbas of the Palestinian Authority. They both expressed their belief in the possibility of peace between Israelis and Palestinians. They discussed ways to advance negotiations and how Arab states could support them. They also condemned the terror attack in Manchester and expressed support for the Riyadh Summit leaders' condemnation of terrorism. They agreed to continue discussions on payments to Palestinian prisoners and improving the Palestinian economy.